 Fig. 1 shows the (like the real thing) effects of the bug-killer 
 tax on farmer health as measured by the mean 
 neurobehavioral score. As expected, health is monotonically increasing in the tax rate because bug-killer 
 use is negatively related to the tax rate, but the slope 
 
